COMMERCIAL USE REQUIRES LICENSE

Commercial deployment, production use, and public-facing services based on
ConvergenceX technology require a valid license, obtained automatically by
locking a refundable security deposit of USD 1,000 equivalent in SOST for
a period of one year (365 days / ~52,560 blocks).

The deposit is returned in full after the lock period. No fees, no
deductions, no interest.

NO LICENSE REQUIRED FOR

- Reading, studying, or auditing the source code
- Academic research and educational use
- Private, non-commercial testing
- Contributing code, documentation, or translations to the project
- Running a personal, non-commercial SOST node

DEPOSIT TERMS

The security deposit is denominated in SOST at the PoPC reference price at
the time of lock. The deposit is returned in SOST, not in USD. The Foundation
makes no representation about the future value of SOST. This is not an
investment product, does not generate yield, and carries no expectation of
profit.

LICENSE VERIFICATION

Licenses are cryptographically signed by the Foundation and verifiable
on-chain without contacting any centralized authority.

For verification: https://sostcore.com/sost-license.html

ENFORCEMENT

The Foundation reserves the right to pursue remedies for unauthorized
commercial use of ConvergenceX technology, in accordance with applicable
intellectual property law.

